abstract = {DNA-binding domain (DBD) is a database of predicted
                  sequence-specific DNA-binding transcription factors (TFs) for
                  all publicly available proteomes. The proteomes have increased
                  from 150 in the initial version of DBD to over 700 in the
                  current version. All predicted TFs must contain a significant
